    "content": "This example application shows how to use the ADC Peripheral library to perform automatic window comparison of converted values. The ADC peripheral is configured to operate in window mode. In this example, Analog input voltage in the range of 0 V to 3.3 V is fed to the ADC input channel AD0. The ADC conversion is triggered by software and converted result is displayed on the console whenever input voltage goes below window lower threshold. ",
    "url": "http://localhost:4000/csp_apps_sam_9x60/apps/adc/adc_automatic_window_comparison/readme.html#description",
